## Example Day Entry

```markdown
### Day 1

The first mention of God's mark—Passover blood as a sign of redemption.

>"It shall be as a sign to you on your hand and as a memorial between your eyes, that the LORD's law may be in your mouth" (Exodus 13:9)

 [Read Exodus 13](https://www.bible.com/bible/114/EXO.13.NKJV)
```

## Notes
- Each week typically has 7 days of readings
- Include a short theme sentence after the Day header to encapsulate the reading's focus
- The blockquote should include a key verse from the chapter
- Always use NKJV translation (code 114) for bible.com links
- Maintain consistent spacing: blank line after header, blank line after theme sentence, blank line after blockquote

